Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Halve, peel and chop the @Red Onion{1} into small pieces.

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then add the onion. Stir together and cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the mince cooks, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 1/2 tsp of @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni.

When boiling, stir the @Macaroni{180%grams} into the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, reserve some pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the macaroni back into the pan, drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together. Set aside for now.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Stir the garlic and half the @Dried Oregano{1%sachet} into the lamb. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Next, pour the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliter} into the mince. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer until the sauce has thickened and reduced by half, ~{12-15%minutes}.

After 10 mins, stir in the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix the remaining dried oregano with the @Panko Breadcrumbs{25%grams} and a drizzle of oil. Season with salt and @ground black pepper{to taste}, then set your herby crumb aside.

Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams} and @Reserved Pasta Water{100%milliliter} into the pan of cooked pasta. Season with salt and pepper, then pop on medium-high heat, stirring gently, to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once thickened, spoon the lamb mixture into an #ovenproof dish{}, then top with the creamy pasta. Sprinkle over the crumb and grill until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Allow your pastitsio style pasta to stand for a couple of mins before sharing between your bowls.

Enjoy!